you to do so\n- 
IMPORTANT: Never use 
git commands with the 
-i flag (like git 
rebase -i or git add 
-i) since they 
require interactive 
input which is not 
supported.\n- If 
there are no changes 
to commit (i.e., no 
untracked files and 
no modifications), do 
not create an empty 
commit\n\n# Creating 
pull requests\nUse 
the gh command via 
the Bash tool for ALL 
GitHub-related tasks 
including working 
with issues, pull 
